@NODE "what" "Whats this?"

    As you may or not (?) know, its less then a year 'till the year 2000.

  As this is quite an important date, various 'countdown' programs have appeared
   and show how long you have left 'till the big 2k.


Unfortunately, all of them seems to be boring old window borders/title bar clocks. @{FG fill} (Yawn!)@{FG text}




    As I had nothing better to do I set out to do a better one.


            Le voila!


  Countdown2000 is countdown program, Screen saverą and bootpic which show how long you've got
   left before all PC's keel over, and also represents the time left as sunrise over the
   millennium dome˛. (Looks like those 'SkyLine' screensavers)


 It also has some other little animations, and makes a big thing of it when the millennium does arive.



                                     @{"Okallydokally!" LINK "main"}



                                 ą - Only works as a screen saver @{i}module@{ui}, see installation notes.
                                 ˛ - Countdown2000 is not affiliated with the dome project in any way.
@ENDNODE

